{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSTextInput","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Layout","text":"Layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Text input is based on several configurable UI elements:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"label"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": It is used to describe the purpose of the input.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In some UI contexts, especially when space is limited or when the input is part of a compact layout (search bars, filters, inline forms), the label can be hidden.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, hiding the label should only be done if the purpose of the input remains clear thanks to a placeholder or contextual icon","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and if the label is still accessible to screen readers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Hiding a label is a design choice that must balance visual simplicity and clarity of intent, without compromising inclusiveness or form guidance.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"placeholder"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": if the text of the text input is empty a placeholder provides a hint or guidance inside the field to suggest expected input.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A prefix and a suffix can be added to give more context.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"leading icon"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": it helps indicate the purpose of the input (magnifying glass for search, envelope for email, phone device for phone number).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Only use a leading icon if it adds clear functional or contextual value.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"trailing action"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": it is used to provide actions related to the field: clear input, toggle password visibility, open a date picker, etc.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Can also indicate status or feedback (error checkmark, loading spinner).","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Outlined-style","text":"Outlined style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", the input is with a subtle background fill and invisible bottom border, creating a softer and more contained look.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Best suited for dense layouts or to enhance visibility.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"outlined"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", the text input is a minimalist design with a transparent background and a visible stroke outlining the field.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This style may be interesting for contexts other than form pages:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When inputs need to feel lightweight and unobtrusive","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In a header (search field)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In a selection\/filtering feature in a product catalog","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["   \/\/ An outlined text input","   OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, isOutlined: true)","","   \/\/ With a localizable and a bundle","   OUDSTextInput(LocalizedStringKey(\"label_wording\"), bundle: Bundle.module, text: $text)"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Rounded-layout","text":"Rounded layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Text input can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To activate the rounded corner behavior, set to true the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedTextInputs"},{"text":" values of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"text":" object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WireframeTheme"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Status","text":"Status"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Five status are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Default neutral appearance, whether empty or filled.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It allows users to click, focus, and type freely without restrictions.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"error"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": The ","type":"text"},{"code":"error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" status indicates that the user input does not meet validation rules or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"expected formatting. It provides immediate visual feedback, typically through a red border,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"error icon, and a clear, accessible error message positioned below the input. The error messages replaces the helper text.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": The ","type":"text"},{"code":"loading","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" state indicates that the system is processing or retrieving data","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"related to the text entered. A progress indicator appears to inform the user that an action is in progress.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"readOnly"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" :The","type":"text"},{"code":"readOnly","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", lets the text visible but not editable","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disabled"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": In ","type":"text"},{"code":"disabled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" status, the field is non-interactive and grayed out to indicate it cannot be changed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Note the SwiftUI ","type":"text"},{"code":"View.disabled()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ignored.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Helpers","text":"Helpers"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Helper text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":":  A supporting text conveys additional information about the input field,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as how it will be used. It should ideally only take up a single line, though may wrap","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to multiple lines if required, and be either persistently visible or visible only on focus.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Helper link"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": If the helper text is not sufficient, it’s possible to offer the user","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an additional help link (the link can be external or open a modal).","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default no haptics are done by the component for the trailing action.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However you should think about cases wher you will have to make the devices vibrates.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can refer to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/design\/human-interface-guidelines\/playing-haptics"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Mandatory-field-indication","text":"Mandatory field indication"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields are mandatory” at the top of your formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Do not use an asterisk at the end of each field label, nor the word “mandatory.”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If not all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields marked with an * are mandatory” at the top of your formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use an asterisk (*) at the end of each mandatory field label, and ensures this is well vocalized.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"UI rendering of the asterisk must be done with ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"bold font weight"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative content color"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" (red on light backgrounds).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the mention “(optional)” at the end of each optional field label. Note that this rule is not systematic, it remains an option, to be used if needed.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If there is only one field in the formular, or if the mandatory nature is obvious (such as login\/password),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"no mention is necessary since the fields are essential to the formular’s functionality.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The text to display and edit","    @State var text: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ Empty text and no placeholder","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text)","","    \/\/ Empty text with placeholder and suffix","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\", suffix: \"@orange.com\")","","    \/\/ Empty text with prefix and suffix","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, prefix: \"Distance\", suffix: \"km\")","","    \/\/ Add a leading icon for more context","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\", suffix: \"@orange.com\", leadingIcon: Image(systemName: \"envelope\"))","","    \/\/ Add a trailing button with local image namde \"ic_cross\" for additional action","    let trailingAction = OUDSTextInput.TrailingAction(icon: Image(\"ic_cross\"), actionHint: \"Delete\") { text = \"\" }","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, trailingAction: trailingAction)","","    \/\/ With helper text","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\",","                  text: $text,","                  placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\",","                  suffix: \"@orange.com\",","                  helperText: \"The email will be automatically completed with @orange.com\")","","    \/\/ With helper link","    @Environment(\\.openURL) private var openUrl","","    let helperLink = OUDSTextInput.HelperLink(text: \"Helper Link\") {","       openUrl.callAsFunction(url)","    }","","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, placeholder: \"Placeholder\", helperLink: helperLink)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, flipLeadingIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Design-documentation","text":"Design documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-text-input"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Themes-rendering","text":"Themes rendering"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Orange","text":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textInput_Orange"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact","text":"Orange Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textInput_OrangeCompact"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Sosh","text":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textInput_Sosh"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe","text":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textInput_Wireframe"}]},{"name":"Version","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.3.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"Since","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.20.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSTextInput","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents13OUDSTextInputV","symbolKind":"struct","title":"OUDSTextInput","roleHeading":"Structure","platforms":[{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"15.0"},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"13.0"},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0"}],"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTextInput"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Text input is a UI element that allows to enter, edit, or select single-line textual data."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Text input is one of the most fundamental form elements used to capture user input such as names, emails, passwords, or search queries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides a visual and interactive affordance for text entry while supporting labels, placeholders, icons, descriptions, and validation feedback."}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/Helperlink","doc:\/\/OUDS